INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_rim3000','letter','1775-09-19','St Johns','QC','CAN','Richard','Montgomery','','Philip','Schuyler','','individual','','Yesterday, I marched, with five hundred men, to the north side of St. John\'s, where we found a party of the King\'s troops, with field-pieces.','ltr_rim3000.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume I., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_rim3001','letter','1775-09-28','St Johns','QC','CAN','Richard','Montgomery','','Philip','Schuyler','','individual','','Since my last of the 24th, we have opened a battery of two twelve-pounders, upon the ship-yards and schooner. She was obliged immediately to haul near the wharf, or rather as near the north end of the fort as she could get','ltr_rim3001.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume I., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_rim3002','letter','1775-10-06','St Johns','QC','CAN','Richard','Montgomery','','Philip','Schuyler','','individual','','Your vigilance and foresight have saved us from the difficulties that threatened us. We are no longer afraid of starving.','ltr_rim3002.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume I., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_rim3003','letter','1775-10-13','St Johns','QC','CAN','Richard','Montgomery','','Philip','Schuyler','','individual','','Some time ago I informed you of my intentions to make my approaches on the west side, as soon as the expected reenforcement enabled me to undertake it.','ltr_rim3003.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume I., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_rim3004','letter','1775-10-22','St Johns','QC','CAN','Richard','Montgomery','','Guy','Carleton','','individual','','I have received information, from different quarters, that the prisoners you have made are treated with cruel and unnecessary severity, being loaded with irons','ltr_rim3004.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume I., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_rim3005','letter','1775-11-01','St Johns','QC','CAN','Richard','Montgomery','','','Preston','','individual','','Having now acquitted my conscience, I must, to save time and prevent trouble, acquaint you, if you do not surrender this day, it will be unnecessary to make any future proposals.','ltr_rim3005.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume I., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_rim3006','letter','1775-11-03','St Johns','QC','CAN','Richard','Montgomery','','Philip','Schuyler','','individual','','I have the pleasure to acquaint you the garrison surrendered last night. This morning, we take possession ; to-morrow, I hope the prisoners will set off.','ltr_rim3006.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume I., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_rim3007','letter','1775-11-12','Montreal','QC','CAN','Richard','Montgomery','','','','','public','The Inhabitants Of Montreal','My anxiety for the fate of Montreal induces me to request, that you will exert yourselves among the inhabitants to prevail on them to enter into such measures as will prevent the necessity of opening my batteries on the town.','ltr_rim3007.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume I., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_rim3008','letter','1775-11-12','Montreal','QC','CAN','Richard','Montgomery','','','','','public','The Inhabitants Of Montreal','The city of Montreal, having neither ammunition, artillery, troops, nor provisions, and having it not in their power to fulfil one article of the treaty, can claim no title to a capitulation.','ltr_rim3008.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume I., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_rim3009','letter','1775-11-13','Montreal','QC','CAN','Richard','Montgomery','','Philip','Schuyler','','individual','','This morning we have taken possession of the town ; I send you their articles of capitulation, with my answer, and hope it may meet with approbation.','ltr_rim3009.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume I., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_rim3010','letter','1775-11-19','Montreal','QC','CAN','Richard','Montgomery','','Philip','Schuyler','','individual','','I have this morning had another express from Colonel Arnold, acquainting me he has crossed the river to the Quebec side ; that he had been near surprising the town ; that it was closely invested','ltr_rim3010.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume I., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_rim3011','letter','1775-11-24','Montreal','QC','CAN','Richard','Montgomery','','Philip','Schuyler','','individual','','It is with great indignation I hear Lieutenant Halsey, whom I left as Assistant Engineer at St. John\'s, to put the barracks in a proper state for the reception of a garrison, has run away without leave','ltr_rim3011.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume I., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_rim3012','letter','1775-12-05','Abraham','QC','CAN','Richard','Montgomery','','Philip','Schuyler','','individual','','The season has proved so favorable as to enable me to join Colonel Arnold at Point-aux-Trembles, where I arrived with the vessels Mr. Prescott made us a present of.','ltr_rim3012.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume I., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_rim3013','letter','1775-12-06','Abraham','QC','CAN','Richard','Montgomery','','Guy','Carleton','','individual','','notwithstanding the cruelty you have shown to the unhappy prisoners you have taken, the feelings of humanity induce me to have recourse to this expedient to save you from the destruction which hangs over your wretched garrison.','ltr_rim3013.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume I., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_rim3014','letter','1775-12-16','Quebec City','QC','CAN','Richard','Montgomery','','David','Wooster','','individual','','Yesterday we opened a battery of five guns and a howitzer, and, with very little effect, I attempted to summon the Governor by a flag of truce. He would not receive any letter.','ltr_rim3014.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume I., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_rim3015','letter','1775-12-18','Quebec City','QC','CAN','Richard','Montgomery','','Philip','Schuyler','','individual','','I have been near a fortnight before Quebec, at the head of upwards of eight hundred men ; a force, you will say, not very adequate to the business in hand.','ltr_rim3015.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume I., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_rim3016','letter','1775-12-26','Quebec City','QC','CAN','Richard','Montgomery','','Philip','Schuyler','','individual','','I then had reason to believe the troops well inclined for a coup-de-main. I have since discovered, to my great mortification, that three companies of Colonel Arnold\'s detachment are very averse from the measure.','ltr_rim3016.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume I., Jared Sparks, 1853');
